  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "Synthetic adversarial UnitOfAssurance for ASME V&V 40 weakness W-AR-05 (comparator absence or mismatch) with defeater type D3 (undercutting — inference method mismatch). The COU requires pulsatile-flow hemolysis prediction for a Class III VAD at MRL 5. The validation activity was conducted under steady-state, constant-speed flow conditions using a mock-loop benchtop experiment. Although a comparator dataset is referenced by name in the validation narrative, the primary validation result object lacks a comparedAgainst link (W-AR-05 trigger). A secondary result carries a comparedAgainst IRI pointing to the steady-state dataset, making the regime mismatch with the pulsatile COU explicit and detectable. Credibility gaps are acknowledged; decision is recorded as Accepted to surface the inference-method mismatch as the adversarial flaw.",
